1. Product Introduction  
Thank you for choosing the X100 Pro Robotic Vacuum Cleaner. Equipped with laser navigation, auto-recharging, mopping function, and remote control via App. Suitable for hard floors, tiles, short-pile carpets, etc.

2. Safety Precautions  
WARNING:  
- Children under 8 and persons with reduced physical/mental abilities must be supervised.  
- Use only the original charging base and battery pack.  
- Turn off the device and unplug the charger before cleaning/maintenance.  
- Do not vacuum water, oil, burning cigarette butts, needles, or threads.  
- Clear away cables, curtain tassels, and small objects from the floor before use.  
- Do not use in wet or high‑temperature areas (e.g., bathroom, near a stove).  

CAUTION:  
- Always empty the dust bin before each use.  
- Place the charging base against a wall, with 1.5m clear space in front and 0.5m on both sides.

3. Package Contents  
- Main unit ×1  
- Auto‑charging base ×1  
- Power adapter ×1  
- Side brushes (1 installed + 2 spare)  
- Dust bin (installed)  
- Water tank & mopping cloth ×1  
- Cleaning brush ×1  
- User manual & warranty card ×1

4. Product Parts Description  
Top: LiDAR sensor, Power/Clean button, Wi‑Fi indicator  
Side: Edge sensor, Charging contacts, Air outlet  
Bottom: Side brush, Main brush, Swivel wheel, Cliff sensors, Battery cover  
Inside: Dust bin latch, HEPA filter

5. Operating Instructions  
5.1 Before Use  
- Remove small objects, wires, and rug tassels from the floor.  
- Place the charging base against a wall and plug it in.  

5.2 Power On & Charging  
- Press and hold the main power button for 3 seconds to turn on.  
- Place the robot on the charging base. You will hear “Charging”. For first use, charge for 5 hours.  

5.3 Start Cleaning  
- Short press the power button: auto clean (bow‑shape path coverage).  
- Short press again: pause; hold 3 seconds: power off.  
- The robot automatically returns to the charging base after cleaning.  

5.4 Mopping Mode  
- Install the water tank, fill with water, and attach the mopping cloth. The robot will start mopping automatically.

6. App Instructions (optional)  
- Download the “RoboSmart” App from the QR code.  
- Add device and select “X100 Pro”.  
- Connect to a 2.4GHz Wi‑Fi network following the prompts.  
- Via the App you can view maps, set virtual walls, schedule cleaning, adjust suction power, etc.

7. Maintenance & Care (recommended weekly)  
- Dust bin: Remove and empty the bin. Rinse the bin and HEPA filter with clean water (dry completely before reuse).  
- Main brush: Open the bottom cover, remove the brush and clear tangled hair.  
- Side brush: Unscrew and remove tangled debris.  
- Cliff sensors & charging contacts: Wipe with a dry soft cloth.  
- Mopping cloth: Wash and dry after each use; remove if not used for a long time.

8. Troubleshooting  

| Problem                      | Possible Cause & Solution                                    |
|------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Cannot power on              | Battery depleted → charge on base for at least 30 minutes    |
| Missed spots or messy path   | LiDAR blocked → clean the sensor area; avoid direct sunlight |
| Fails to return to base      | Obstacles near base or base moved → clear and reposition     |
| No water / poor mopping      | Water tank not sealed / cloth dirty → reinstall tank, clean cloth |
| Unusual noise                | Main or side brush tangled → turn off and remove debris        |

9. Technical Specifications  
- Rated voltage: 14.4V  
- Rated power: 40W  
- Battery: 5200mAh Li‑ion  
- Dust bin capacity: 600mL  
- Water tank capacity: 300mL  
- Noise level: ≤65dB (standard mode)  
- Dimensions: 350×350×98mm  

